Comments: A 31-year-old female drowned after being swept by rip currents.
Statement/advisory/warnings: CFW-High Surf Advisory & High Rip Current Risk

title: x63
Comments: Emergency Managers reported that a 13 year old (male) minor was swept away by strong rip currents in Montones beach (Pocita Azul) in the municipality of Isabela. After around a week of searching the body was not found; authorities have stated that he is presumed dead and was carried out to sea.
Statement/advisory/warnings: CFW-High Rip Current Risk

title: x64
Comments: Two people were swept away by rip currents in Flamenco Beach. One was rescued, the other person drowned. The police confirmed that it was a 42-year old male that drowned.
Statement/advisory/warnings: CFW-High Rip Current Risk

title: x65
Comments: Four people were swept away by rip currents at Playa Escondida, Fajardo. Emergency Managers rescued three out of the four individuals.
Statement/advisory/warnings: CFW-High Rip Current Risk & High Surf Advisory

title: x66
Comments: A 63-year-old woman body was recovered from Isla Roque Beach during the overnight hours.
Statement/advisory/warnings: CFW-High Rip Current Risk & High Surf Advisory

title: x70
Comments: EM reported drowning at Huntington State Park. Reported as a non-swimmer. Attempted to assist a young child in strong longshore, got separated and teen drowned.
Statement/advisory/warnings: BH.S for Strong Longshore Current

title: x73
Comments: 8 people caught in rip reported to WFO following day. Teen was trying to save his girlfriend's sister.

title: x74
Comments: 70yo male jumped in water to help grandson who was on a boogie board that got pulled out by a rip. Grandson survived but the grandfather did not.
Statement/advisory/warnings: Rip Current Statement for high rip risk issued at 11am (moderate risk prior)

title: x75
Comments: LSR *** 1 Fatal *** A 58-year-old adult male drowned after trying to save children in the ocean at Fort Fisher. Life saving measures were performed immediately in the water and on land, but were unsuccessful. Fort Fisher lifeguards reported over 50 rip current related rescues that day. 5 SSW Carolina Beach, NC
Statement/advisory/warnings: Moderate rip risk

title: x76
Comments: Community members who knew the victim state drowning was rip current related. Medical examiner's report confirms (does mention alcohol and lack of swimming ability).

title: x78
Statement/advisory/warnings: Moderate rip risk

title: x80
Comments:
2 brothers went into the water in a red
flagged area that had signs saying Danger
Drowning Risk from Rip Currents. No 
lifeguards in that area. Good samaritans
rescued one, but the other was not found.
His body washed up on Saturday 7/29.
Statement/advisory/warnings:
Rip Statement in Effect for High Risk of 
Rip Currents

title: x81
Comments:
5 teens went runing into the water, 
one went farther than the others and 
went missing. His body washed ashore
several hour later.
Statement/advisory/warnings: Moderate Risk
Time of Occurence:
Just after 6pm - 
Lifeguards had just 
left for the day

title: x82
Location of Incident: Surf City, NC (1700 block of South Shore Drive)
Statement/advisory/warnings: Rip Current Statement for High Rip Risk (due to Franklin swells)

title: x83
Location of Incident: North Myrtle Beach, SC (6th Ave S)
Comments: Man went missing after last being seen swimming in North Myrtle Beach. Body found a few hours later.
Statement/advisory/warnings: Rip Current Statement for High Rip Risk (Idalia had just exited the area)

title: x90
Comments: rescue drowning

title: x91
Location of Incident: Portage Lakefront and Riverwalk Beach. IN
